<section class="calloutBox">
  <h2>What Most Gardeners Should Actually Use</h2>

  <p>
    Use a soft, strong support net or sling attached to your trellis as soon as fruit begins to develop. Focus on even weight distribution and secure attachment rather than tight support.
  </p>

  <p>
    This prevents stress on the vine and allows the fruit to grow naturally.
  </p>

